Description: Lip and wall sherd of East Greek (South Ionian?) pottery cup; interior glazed with added red band; exterior: top of rim glazed, handle zone reserved; streakily glazed below; inscription in reserved handle-zone.
Findspot: Excavated/Findspot: Sanctuary of Apollo (Naukratis) (said to be)
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GE.880)
